<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Quote Maker</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../../public/styles/index.css">
<link rel="icon" href="/public/images/message.png">

</head>
<body>
    <%- include('../partials/base.ejs') %>
    <%- include('../partials/header.ejs') %>

    <div class="form_">
        <form action="" method="">
            <div class="top___">
                <h2>Quote Maker Tool</h2>
                <p>Try Random Quote <i class="fa-solid fa-shuffle"></i></p>
            </div>
            <div><textarea autofocus required id="quote" cols="30" rows="10" placeholder="Enter Quote"></textarea></div>
            <div><input  type="text" id="author" placeholder="Author (optional)"></div>
            <button>Generate <i class="fa-solid fa-arrows-rotate"></i></button>
        </form>
    </div>

    <div class="contents">
        <!-- <h1 class="main_">Quote maker / quote generator online tool</h1> -->

        <div class="qna">
            <h2>What is Quote Maker / Quote Generator?</h2>
            <p>
               <b>Quote maker</b>  or <b>quote generator</b>  is a online tool for generating quotes with image as background.
                It has a lots of templates to use. This tool is free to use.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="qna">
            <h2>How to make quote background image with Quote Maker?</h2>
            <p>Unlike other tools where you need to edit yourself setting the accurate font size, images color adjustments and all.
               Quote maker is easy to use for all kinds of person. You can follow below steps to create your quote with background image after you land to quotemaker.com.
            </p>
            <ul class="how_to">
                <li>First go to <a style="color: blue; font-weight: 600;" href="https://quotemaker.frontendmonster.com">Quote Maker</a> website </li>
                <li>You will see form where you have to enter the <b>Quote</b> and <b>Author(optional)</b> of your choice</li>
                <li>If you have no idea of quote then you can click <b>Try Random Quote</b> button in top right of form</li>
                <li>After you enter the quote click <b>Generate</b></li>
                <li>You will be redirected to another page and you will see different templates</li>
                <li>Click <b>Download</b> button to download the quote image and click <b>Share</b> button if you want to directly share to social media</li>
                <li>To change the template click your choice of template below <b>More Templates</b></li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="qna">
            <h2>Features of Quote Maker</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Eye catching templates</li>
                <li>Easy to use for everyone</li>
                <li>Social media sharing options</li>
                <li>Different fonts and backgrounds</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

    </div>

<%- include('../partials/footer.ejs') %>

<script>
    var quoteData = JSON.parse(window.localStorage.getItem("quoteData"))
    if(!quoteData){
        const quoteData = {
            quote:'"If you are not willing to risk the usual, you will have to settle for the ordinary."',
            author:"- Jim Rohn"  
        }
        window.localStorage.setItem("quoteData",JSON.stringify(quoteData))
    }
    const form = document.querySelector(".form_ form")
    const quote = document.getElementById("quote")
    const author = document.getElementById("author")
    form.addEventListener('submit',(e)=>{
        e.preventDefault()
        if(quote.value){
            const quoteData = {
            quote:quote.value,
            author:author.value
            }
            window.localStorage.setItem("quoteData",JSON.stringify(quoteData))
            window.location.href = "/quote/quote-maker"
        }
    })
</script>    
</body>
</html>